#X obj 434 751 float2imp~;
#X obj 185 669 bng 21 250 50 0 empty empty empty 0 -10 0 12 #dfdfdf #000000 #000000;
#X text 521 742 default impulse value is 1, f 17;
#X text 73 570 The [float2imp~] object from ELSE converts control rate floats/bangs to impulses (a signal where a single sample is non zero while the ones next to it are zeros). Since it is an abstraction based on [vline~] it does this with sample accuracy and can convert more than one bang within an audio block. Below we convert a float to an impulse whose amplitude corresponds to the float value (1 in this case \, which is also the default value)., f 87;
#X text 470 360 The [float2sig~] object is an abstraction based on [vline~] and takes a ramp time as an argument. It can be abbreviatted as [f2s~], f 33;
